[{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = GeneticsMakie","category":"page"},{"location":"#GeneticsMakie","page":"Home","title":"GeneticsMakie","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for GeneticsMakie.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Modules = [GeneticsMakie]","category":"page"},{"location":"#GeneticsMakie.coordinategenes-Tuple{AbstractString, Real, Real, DataFrames.DataFrame, Real}","page":"Home","title":"GeneticsMakie.coordinategenes","text":"coordinategenes(chromosome::AbstractString, range1::Real, range2::Real, gencode::DataFrame)\n\nSubset gencode to a given chromosome and genomic range between range1 and range2, and determine coordinates of exons for each gene residing in the genomic region.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeneticsMakie.coordinateisforms-Tuple{AbstractString, DataFrames.DataFrame, Union{Nothing, AbstractVector{<:AbstractString}}, Real, Bool, Symbol}","page":"Home","title":"GeneticsMakie.coordinateisforms","text":"coordinateisforms(gene::AbstractString, gencode::DataFrame, orderby::Union{Nothing, AbstractVector{<:AbstractString}}, height::Real, text::Bool, textpos::Symbol)\n\nSubset gencode to a gene and determine coordinates of exons for each isoform.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeneticsMakie.parsegtf!-Tuple{DataFrames.DataFrame}","page":"Home","title":"GeneticsMakie.parsegtf!","text":"parsegtf!(gencode::DataFrame)\n\nParse gencode by extracting information from the ninth info column.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeneticsMakie.plotgenes!-Tuple{Makie.MakieLayout.Axis, AbstractString, DataFrames.DataFrame}","page":"Home","title":"GeneticsMakie.plotgenes!","text":"plotgenes!(ax::Axis, gene::AbstractString, gencode::DataFrame; window, height, highlight)\n\nPlot collapsed gene bodies for genes within a certain window around gene.  The default window is 1 Mb. Optionally, height of exons can be adjusted using  height and genes can be highlighted via highlight.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeneticsMakie.plotgenes!-Tuple{Makie.MakieLayout.Axis, AbstractString, Real, DataFrames.DataFrame}","page":"Home","title":"GeneticsMakie.plotgenes!","text":"plotgenes!(ax::Axis, chromosome::AbstractString, bp::Real, gencode::DataFrame; window, height, highlight)\n\nPlot collapsed gene bodies for genes within a given chromosome and a certain window around a genomic coordinate bp. The default window is 1 Mb. Optionally,  height of exons can be adjusted using height and genes can be highlighted via highlight.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeneticsMakie.plotgenes!-Tuple{Makie.MakieLayout.Axis, AbstractString, Real, Real, DataFrames.DataFrame}","page":"Home","title":"GeneticsMakie.plotgenes!","text":"plotgenes!(ax::Axis, chromosome::AbstractString, range1::Real, range2::Real, gencode::DataFrame; height, highlight)\n\nPlot collapsed gene bodies for genes within a given chromosome and genomic range  between range1 and range2. Optionally, height of exons can be adjusted using height and genes can be highlighted via highlight.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeneticsMakie.plotisoforms!-Tuple{Makie.MakieLayout.Axis, AbstractString, DataFrames.DataFrame}","page":"Home","title":"GeneticsMakie.plotisoforms!","text":"plotisoforms!(ax::Axis, gene::AbstractString, gencode::DataFrame; orderby, height, text, textpos)\n\nPlot each isoform of a given gene in a separate row. Optionally, order of isoforms can be changed by orderby, height of exons can be adjusted using height, and the presence or absence of text label of isoforms can be specified using text with its position textpos.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#GeneticsMakie.plotld!-Tuple{Makie.MakieLayout.Axis, AbstractMatrix}","page":"Home","title":"GeneticsMakie.plotld!","text":"plotld!(LD::AbstractMatrix)\n\nVisualize a correlation matrix LD with the diagonal elements on the x-axis.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"}]
